  "english": [
    "<b>Rabbi Abba raised an objection</b> from a later mishna (66a): If one said: <b>I will not marry ugly so-and-so</b> as <b>that is <i>konam</i></b> for me, <b>and she is</b> in fact <b>beautiful,</b> or if he called her <b>black, and she is</b> in fact <b>white,</b> or if he called her <b>short, and she is</b> in fact <b>tall, he is permitted to her. Not because she</b> was <b>ugly and became beautiful, black and became white,</b> or <b>short and became tall,</b> but <b>rather,</b> because <b>the vow was mistaken</b> from the outset. <b>Granted, according to Rav Huna, who said that he is considered like one who makes his vow dependent on a matter,</b> the mishna here <b>taught</b> the case of one who <b>makes his vow dependent on a matter, and it taught</b> there the case of <b>a mistaken vow. But according to Rabbi Yoḥanan, who said</b> that the mishna here is referring to a situation where the dog had <b>already died, or</b> the father had <b>already repented, why do I</b> need the mishna <b>to teach</b> the <i>halakha</i> of <b>a mistaken vow twice?</b> The Gemara comments: This is <b>difficult.</b>",
    "<strong>MISHNA:</strong> <b>And Rabbi Meir further said:</b> The halakhic authorities <b>may broach</b> dissolution <b>with him from that which is written in the Torah, and</b> they <b>may say to him: Had you known that</b> through your vow <b>you are transgressing</b> the prohibition <b>“you shall not take vengeance”</b> (Leviticus 19:18) <b>and</b> the prohibition <b>“nor bear any grudge”</b> (Leviticus 19:18), <b>and</b> the prohibition <b>“you shall not hate your brother in your heart”</b> (Leviticus 19:17), and <b>“you shall love your neighbor as yourself”</b> (Leviticus 19:18), as well as <b>“and your brother</b> should <b>live with you”</b> (Leviticus 25:36), <b>as he,</b> the one prohibited by the vow, <b>is poor and</b> now <b>you are not able to provide him</b> with a livelihood due to your vow, would you have vowed in that case? If <b>he said</b> in reply: <b>Had I known that it is so,</b> that my vow involved all these prohibitions, <b>I would not have vowed; it is dissolved.</b>",
    "<strong>GEMARA:</strong> <b>Rav Huna bar Rav Ketina said to the Sages:</b> But <b>let</b> the one who stated the vow <b>say</b> with regard to the last claim: <b>All who become poor do not fall upon me;</b> it is not my responsibility to provide for this specific poor person. <b>What is placed upon me to provide for him together with everyone else, I will provide</b> to <b>him</b> when I give money to those collecting for the communal charity fund. <b>They said to him: I say</b> that <b>anyone who falls</b> into poverty and requires assistance <b>does not fall into the hands of the</b> charity <b>collector first.</b> Rather, his descent begins when he encounters hard times, and it is at this stage that he may require individual, direct support to prevent him from plunging into a state of absolute poverty.",
    "<strong>MISHNA:</strong> The halakhic authorities <b>may broach</b> dissolution <b>with a man by</b> raising the issue of <b>his wife’s marriage contract.</b> If one takes a vow that would require him to divorce his wife, e.g., he prohibits her from deriving benefit from him, his vow may be dissolved by asking him whether he had considered how difficult it would be to pay her marriage contract.",
    "The mishna relates: <b>And an incident</b> occurred <b>with regard to one who vowed</b> against <b>his wife</b> deriving <b>benefit from</b> him, <b>and her marriage contract was</b> worth <b>four hundred dinars. And he came before Rabbi Akiva, and he obligated him to give her</b> the payment of <b>her marriage contract. He said to</b> Rabbi Akiva: <b>My teacher,</b> my <b>father left eight hundred dinars</b> as our inheritance, of which <b>my brother took four hundred and I</b> took <b>four hundred. Isn’t it enough for</b> my wife <b>to take two hundred and I</b> will have <b>two hundred? Rabbi Akiva said to him:</b> Your claim is not accepted, as <b>even if you sell the hair on your head, you must give her</b> the full payment of <b>her marriage contract. He said to him: Had I known that it was so,</b> that I would have to give her all my property, <b>I would not have vowed. And Rabbi Akiva permitted her</b> to derive benefit from him.",
    "<strong>GEMARA:</strong> The Gemara questions the comment made by Rabbi Akiva, that even if the man were to sell the hair on his head, he must pay her the full sum of her marriage contract: <b>Is movable property mortgaged for</b> the payment of <b>a marriage contract?</b> The Rabbis maintain that only land owned by the husband is mortgaged for the payment of a marriage contract, so why should he have to sell the hair on his head? <b>Abaye said:</b> He said that the father had left <b>land worth eight hundred dinars,</b> and he received four hundred dinars’ worth of land, so all of his land is equal in value to his wife’s marriage contract. The Gemara raises a difficulty: <b>But</b> the mishna <b>teaches</b> that he must pay even from: <b>The hair on his head, and the hair on his head is movable property.</b> The Gemara answers: <b>This is what he said:</b> You must pay the marriage contract from the land <b>even</b> if <b>you</b> will need to <b>sell</b> the <b>hair on your head and</b> use the proceeds from the sale in order to <b>eat,</b> as you will have no other source of income.",
    "The Gemara poses a question: <b>Should you conclude from</b> the mishna that <b>arrangements are not made with a creditor,</b> but instead, the entire sum is collected immediately, without reaching an agreement with the husband’s creditors to leave him some money to support himself? The Gemara refutes this suggestion: <b>Rav Naḥman, son of Rabbi Yitzḥak, said:</b>"
  ],
  "gemara": [
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "<span class=\"sentence\" id=\"0\" type=\"start\">&star;</span>מֵתִיב <span class=\"name-reference-marker name-reference-amora\" data-sage-type=\"amora\" title=\"Rabbi Akiva I, second-generation Amora\" data-authority-id=\"6\" data-full-name=\"Rabbi Akiva I\" data-name-he=\"רבי אבא\">רַבִּי אַבָּא</span>: ״קֻוֽנָּם שֶׁאֵינִי נוֹשֵׂא לִפְלוֹנִית",
      "segment_ids": [
        0
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "כְּעוּרָה״, וַהֲרֵי הִיא נָאָה. ״שְׁחוֹרָה״, וַהֲרֵי הִיא",
      "segment_ids": [
        0
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "לְבָנָה. ״קְצָרָה״, וַהֲרֵי הִיא אֲרוּכָּה — מוּתָּר בָּהּ.",
      "segment_ids": [
        0
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "לֹא מִפְּנֵי שֶׁכְּעוּרָה וְנַעֲשֵׂת נָאֶה, שְׁחוֹרָה",
      "segment_ids": [
        0
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "וְנַעֲשֵׂת לְבָנָה, קְצָרָה וְנַעֲשֵׂת אֲרוּכָּה — אֶלָּא",
      "segment_ids": [
        0
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "שֶׁהַנֶּדֶר טָעוּת. בִּשְׁלָמָא <span class=\"name-reference-marker name-reference-amora\" data-sage-type=\"amora\" title=\"Rav Huna I, second-generation Amora\" data-authority-id=\"895\" data-full-name=\"Rav Huna I\" data-name-he=\"רב הונא\">לְרַב הוּנָא</span> דְּאָמַר",
      "segment_ids": [
        0
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "נַעֲשָׂה כְּתוֹלֶה נִדְרוֹ בְּדָבָר: תְּנָא תּוֹלֶה נִדְרוֹ",
      "segment_ids": [
        0
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "בְּדָבָר, וּתְנָא נֶדֶר טָעוּת. אֶלָּא <span class=\"name-reference-marker name-reference-amora\" data-sage-type=\"amora\" title=\"Rabbi Yoḥanan II, second-generation Amora\" data-authority-id=\"1570\" data-full-name=\"Rabbi Yoḥanan II\" data-name-he=\"רבי יוחנן\">לְרַבִּי יוֹחָנָן</span>,",
      "segment_ids": [
        0
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "דְּאָמַר כְּבָר מֵת וּכְבָר עָשָׂה תְּשׁוּבָה, לְמָה",
      "segment_ids": [
        0
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "לִי לְמִתְנֵי תְּרֵי זִימְנֵי נֶדֶר טָעוּת? קַשְׁיָא<span class=\"sugya-marker sugya-marker-vilna-piska\" data-sugya-kind=\"vilna-piska\" data-sugya-id=\"229\" data-raw-symbol=\"׃\">׃</span>",
      "segment_ids": [
        0
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "<span class=\"sugya-marker sugya-marker-steinsaltz\" data-sugya-kind=\"steinsaltz\" data-sugya-id=\"224\" data-sentence-id=\"1\" data-steinsaltz-label=\"א משנה\">§</span> <span class=\"sentence\" id=\"1\" type=\"start\">&star;</span><big><strong>מַתְנִי׳</strong></big> וְעוֹד אָמַר <span class=\"name-reference-marker name-reference-tanna\" data-sage-type=\"tanna\" title=\"Rabbi Meir, fifth-generation Tanna\" data-authority-id=\"2068\" data-full-name=\"Rabbi Meir\" data-name-he=\"רבי מאיר\">רַבִּי מֵאִיר</span>: פּוֹתְחִין לוֹ מִן",
      "segment_ids": [
        1
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "הַכָּתוּב שֶׁבַּתּוֹרָה, וְאוֹמְרִין לוֹ: אִילּוּ הָיִיתָ יוֹדֵעַ",
      "segment_ids": [
        1
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "שֶׁאַתָּה עוֹבֵר עַל ״לֹא תִקֹּם״, וְעַל ״לֹא תִטֹּר״,",
      "segment_ids": [
        1
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "וְעַל ״לֹא תִשְׂנָא אֶת אָחִיךָ בִּלְבָבֶךָ״, ״וְאָהַבְתָּ",
      "segment_ids": [
        1
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "לְרֵעֲךָ כָּמוֹךָ״, ״וְחֵי אָחִיךָ עִמָּךְ״, שֶׁהוּא עָנִי וְאֵין",
      "segment_ids": [
        1
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "אַתָּה יָכוֹל לְפַרְנָסוֹ. אָמַר: אִילּוּ הָיִיתִי יוֹדֵעַ",
      "segment_ids": [
        1
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "שֶׁהוּא כֵּן, לֹא הָיִיתִי נוֹדֵר — הֲרֵי זֶה מוּתָּר<span class=\"sugya-marker sugya-marker-vilna-piska\" data-sugya-kind=\"vilna-piska\" data-sugya-id=\"230\" data-raw-symbol=\"׃\">׃</span>",
      "segment_ids": [
        1
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "<span class=\"sugya-marker sugya-marker-steinsaltz\" data-sugya-kind=\"steinsaltz\" data-sugya-id=\"225\" data-sentence-id=\"2\" data-steinsaltz-label=\"ב גמרא\">§</span> <span class=\"sentence\" id=\"2\" type=\"start\">&star;</span><big><strong>גְּמָ׳</strong></big> אָמַר לְהוּ <span class=\"name-reference-marker name-reference-amora\" data-sage-type=\"amora\" title=\"Rav Ḥanina bar Rav Ketina, third and fourth-generation Amora\" data-authority-id=\"1197\" data-full-name=\"Rav Ḥanina bar Rav Ketina\" data-name-he=\"רב חנא בר קטינא\">רַב הוּנָא בַּר רַב קַטִּינָא</span> לְרַבָּנַן:",
      "segment_ids": [
        2
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "נֵימָא, כֹּל דְּמִעֲנֵי לָאו עֲלַי נָפֵיל. מַאי דְּמָטֵי",
      "segment_ids": [
        2
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "לִי לְפַרְנְסוֹ — בַּהֲדֵי כּוּלֵּי עָלְמָא מְפַרְנַסְנָא לֵיהּ. אָמְרִי לֵיהּ:",
      "segment_ids": [
        2
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "אֲנִי אוֹמֵר כׇּל הַנּוֹפֵל, אֵינוֹ נוֹפֵל לִידֵי גַבַּאי",
      "segment_ids": [
        2
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "תְּחִלָּה<span class=\"sugya-marker sugya-marker-vilna-piska\" data-sugya-kind=\"vilna-piska\" data-sugya-id=\"231\" data-raw-symbol=\"׃\">׃</span> <span class=\"sugya-marker sugya-marker-steinsaltz\" data-sugya-kind=\"steinsaltz\" data-sugya-id=\"226\" data-sentence-id=\"3\" data-steinsaltz-label=\"ג משנה\">§</span> <span class=\"sentence\" id=\"3\" type=\"start\">&star;</span><big><strong>מַתְנִי׳</strong></big> פּוֹתְחִין לָאָדָם בִּכְתוּבַּת",
      "segment_ids": [
        3
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "אִשְׁתּוֹ. <span class=\"sentence\" id=\"4\" type=\"start\">&star;</span>וּמַעֲשֶׂה בְּאֶחָד שֶׁנָּדַר מֵאִשְׁתּוֹ הֲנָאָה,",
      "segment_ids": [
        4
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "וְהָיְתָה כְּתוּבָּתָהּ אַרְבַּע מֵאוֹת דִּינָרִים. וּבָא לִפְנֵי <span class=\"name-reference-marker name-reference-tanna\" data-sage-type=\"tanna\" title=\"Rabbi Akiva I, fourth-generation Tanna\" data-authority-id=\"2465\" data-full-name=\"Rabbi Akiva I\" data-name-he=\"רבי עקיבא בן יוסף\">רַבִּי עֲקִיבָא</span>,",
      "segment_ids": [
        4
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "וְחִיְּיבוֹ לִיתֵּן לָהּ כְּתוּבָּתָהּ. אָמַר לוֹ: <span class=\"name-reference-marker name-reference-tanna\" data-sage-type=\"tanna\" title=\"Rabbi Yehuda HaNasi, sixth-generation Tanna\" data-authority-id=\"1508\" data-full-name=\"Rabbi Yehuda HaNasi\" data-name-he=\"רבי יהודה הנשיא\">רַבִּי</span>, שְׁמוֹנֶה",
      "segment_ids": [
        4
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "מֵאוֹת דִּינָרִין הִנִּיחַ <span class=\"name-reference-marker name-reference-amora\" data-sage-type=\"amora\" title=\"of Rav, first-generation Amora\" data-authority-id=\"2578\" data-full-name=\"of Rav\" data-name-he=\"רב\">אַבָּא</span>. נָטַל אָחִי אַרְבַּע מֵאוֹת,",
      "segment_ids": [
        4
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "וַאֲנִי אַרְבַּע מֵאוֹת. לֹא דַּיָּה שֶׁתִּטּוֹל הִיא מָאתַיִם",
      "segment_ids": [
        4
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "וַאֲנִי מָאתַיִם? אָמַר לוֹ <span class=\"name-reference-marker name-reference-tanna\" data-sage-type=\"tanna\" title=\"Rabbi Akiva I, fourth-generation Tanna\" data-authority-id=\"2465\" data-full-name=\"Rabbi Akiva I\" data-name-he=\"רבי עקיבא בן יוסף\">רַבִּי עֲקִיבָא</span>: אֲפִילּוּ אַתָּה מוֹכֵר שְׂעַר רֹאשְׁךָ —",
      "segment_ids": [
        4
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "אַתָּה נוֹתֵן לָהּ כְּתוּבָּתָהּ. אָמַר לוֹ:",
      "segment_ids": [
        4
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "אִילּוּ הָיִיתִי יוֹדֵעַ שֶׁהוּא כֵּן — לֹא הָיִיתִי נוֹדֵר.",
      "segment_ids": [
        4
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "וְהִתִּירָהּ <span class=\"name-reference-marker name-reference-tanna\" data-sage-type=\"tanna\" title=\"Rabbi Akiva I, fourth-generation Tanna\" data-authority-id=\"2465\" data-full-name=\"Rabbi Akiva I\" data-name-he=\"רבי עקיבא בן יוסף\">רַבִּי עֲקִיבָא</span><span class=\"sugya-marker sugya-marker-vilna-piska\" data-sugya-kind=\"vilna-piska\" data-sugya-id=\"232\" data-raw-symbol=\"׃\">׃</span> <span class=\"sugya-marker sugya-marker-steinsaltz\" data-sugya-kind=\"steinsaltz\" data-sugya-id=\"227\" data-sentence-id=\"5\" data-steinsaltz-label=\"ד גמרא\">§</span> <span class=\"sentence\" id=\"5\" type=\"start\">&star;</span><big><strong>גְּמָ׳</strong></big> מִטַּלְטְלֵי מִי",
      "segment_ids": [
        5
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "מִשְׁתַּעְבְּדִי לִכְתוּבָה? אָמַר <span class=\"name-reference-marker name-reference-amora\" data-sage-type=\"amora\" title=\"Abaye, fourth-generation Amora\" data-authority-id=\"121\" data-full-name=\"Abaye\" data-name-he=\"אביי\">אַבָּיֵי</span>: קַרְקַע שָׁוָה",
      "segment_ids": [
        5
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "שְׁמוֹנֶה מֵאוֹת דִּינָר. וְהָקָתָנֵי: ״שְׂעַר רֹאשׁוֹ״, וּשְׂעַר",
      "segment_ids": [
        5
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "רֹאשׁוֹ מִטַּלְטְלֵי הוּא! הָכִי קָאָמַר: אֲפִילּוּ אַתָּה מוֹכֵר",
      "segment_ids": [
        5
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "שְׂעַר רֹאשְׁךָ וְאוֹכֵל. <span class=\"sentence\" id=\"6\" type=\"start\">&star;</span>שָׁמְעַתְּ מִינַּהּ אֵין",
      "segment_ids": [
        6
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "מְסַדְּרִין לְבַעַל חוֹב? אָמַר <span class=\"name-reference-marker name-reference-unknown\" data-sage-type=\"unknown\" title=\"Rav Naḥman, son of\" data-authority-id=\"21205\" data-full-name=\"Rav Naḥman, son of\" data-name-he=\"רב נחמן ברבי יצחק\">רַב נַחְמָן בְּרַבִּי יִצְחָק</span>:",
      "segment_ids": [
        6
      ]
    }
  ],
  "rashi": [
    {
      "width": "450px",
      "right": "",
      "left": "0px",
      "text": "מתיב רבי אבא וכו' והרי היא נאה: <b>אֶלָּא שֶׁהַנֶּדֶר <span class=\"dh-divergent\">בטעות</span></b> מעיקרא",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Nedarim 65b:1:2",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        0
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "450px",
      "right": "",
      "left": "0px",
      "text": "ולא הוי נדר: <b>בִּשְׁלָמָא לְרַב הוּנָא.</b> תנא רישא תולה נדר בדבר",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Nedarim 65b:1:3",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        0
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "450px",
      "right": "",
      "left": "0px",
      "text": "וסיפא תנא תולה נדר בטעות דאינו נדר: אלא לרבי יוחנן כו':",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Nedarim 65b:1:3",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        0
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "450px",
      "right": "",
      "left": "0px",
      "text": "<b>מַתְנִי׳ <span class=\"dh-divergent\">על</span> <span class=\"dh-divergent\">לא</span> <span class=\"dh-divergent\">תקום</span> <span class=\"dh-divergent\">ולא</span> <span class=\"dh-divergent\">תטור</span>.</b> שאם בקשת ממנו כלי ולא השאילך",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Nedarim 65b:2:1",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        3
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "",
      "left": "0px",
      "text": "והדרתו הנאתך או שעשה לך דבר",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Nedarim 65b:2:1",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        3
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "",
      "left": "0px",
      "text": ". שלא כהוגן ומתוך שנאה. הדרתו",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Nedarim 65b:2:1",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        3
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "",
      "left": "0px",
      "text": "והתורה אמרה לא תשנא את אחיך",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Nedarim 65b:2:1",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        3
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "",
      "left": "0px",
      "text": "בלבבך התורה הזקיקתו לפרנסו",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Nedarim 65b:2:1",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        3
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "",
      "left": "0px",
      "text": "ולאוהבו ולהחיותו: <b><span class=\"dh-divergent\">שמא</span> <span class=\"dh-divergent\">יעני</span> <span class=\"dh-divergent\">ואי</span></b>",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Nedarim 65b:2:2",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        2
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "",
      "left": "0px",
      "text": "<b>אַתָּה יָכוֹל לְפַרְנָסוֹ</b> מחמת נדרך:",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Nedarim 65b:2:2",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        2
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "",
      "left": "0px",
      "text": "<b><span class=\"dh-divergent\">ואם</span> אָמַר: אִילּוּ הָיִיתִי יוֹדֵעַ.</b> בשעת",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Nedarim 65b:2:3",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        2
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "",
      "left": "0px",
      "text": "הנדר בכל אזהרות הללו לא הייתי",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Nedarim 65b:2:3",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        2
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "",
      "left": "0px",
      "text": "נודר: <b>גְּמָ׳ <span class=\"dh-divergent\">ונימא</span> <span class=\"dh-divergent\">כל</span> <span class=\"dh-divergent\">דמיעני</span>.</b>",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Nedarim 65b:3:1",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        4
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "",
      "left": "0px",
      "text": "אמאי פותח לו שמא יעני לימא ליה",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Nedarim 65b:3:1",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        4
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "",
      "left": "0px",
      "text": "מדיר לאו כל דמיעני נפול עלי",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Nedarim 65b:3:1",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        4
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "",
      "left": "0px",
      "text": "לפרנסו ימנו לו גבאי לפרנסו ומאי",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Nedarim 65b:3:1",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        4
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "",
      "left": "0px",
      "text": "דמטי לדידי למיהב לפרנסתו: <b>בַּהֲדֵי</b>",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Nedarim 65b:3:2",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        3
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "",
      "left": "0px",
      "text": "<b><span class=\"dh-divergent\">כ&quot;ע</span> מְפַרְנַסְנָא לֵיהּ</b> ואמאי מוזקק",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Nedarim 65b:3:2",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        3
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "",
      "left": "0px",
      "text": "אני לפרנסו טפי משאר עלמא: <b><span class=\"dh-divergent\">הא</span></b>",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Nedarim 65b:6:5",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        4
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "",
      "left": "0px",
      "text": "<b>לֹא <span class=\"dh-divergent\">מצי</span> <span class=\"dh-divergent\">טעון</span> <span class=\"dh-divergent\">דכל</span> <span class=\"dh-divergent\">הנופל</span>.</b> בעניות",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Nedarim 65b:6:5",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        4
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "",
      "left": "0px",
      "text": "אינו נופל לידי גבאי תחילה אלא",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Nedarim 65b:6:5",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        4
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "",
      "left": "0px",
      "text": "קרובים מתגלגלין עמו: <b>מתני&#x27; אתה.</b>",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Nedarim 65b:6:5",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        4
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "",
      "left": "0px",
      "text": "<b>מוכר</b> <b>שער</b> <b>ראשך.</b> מפרש בגמרא:",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Nedarim 65b:6:5",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        4
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "",
      "left": "0px",
      "text": "<b>ואמר.</b> הבעל אילו הייתי יודע כו':"
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "",
      "left": "0px",
      "text": "<b>גמ&#x27; ש&quot;מ.</b> מדקאמר ח' מאות זוז"
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "",
      "left": "0px",
      "text": "הניח לנו אבא רצונה ליטול מאתים"
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "",
      "left": "0px",
      "text": "ש\"מ דמטלטלי משתעבדי לכתובה"
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "",
      "left": "0px",
      "text": "והא קי\"ל (<a href=\"/ketubot/81b\">כתובות פא:</a>) דלא משתעבדי:"
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "",
      "left": "0px",
      "text": "<b>אמר אביי.</b> ה\"ק קרקע שוה ח' מאות"
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "",
      "left": "0px",
      "text": "זוז כו': <b>והא קתני אפי&#x27; אתה מוכר.</b>"
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "",
      "left": "0px",
      "text": "<b>שער</b> <b>ראשך.</b> ומשמע דקאמר אפי'"
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "",
      "left": "0px",
      "text": "אין לך להשלים כתובה אלא משער"
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "",
      "left": "0px",
      "text": "ראשך זקוק אתה למוכרו ולהשלים"
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "",
      "left": "0px",
      "text": "לה: <b>ושער ראשו מטלטלי הוא.</b> דכל"
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "",
      "left": "0px",
      "text": "העומד ליגזוז כגזוז דמי: <b>ה&quot;ק.</b> ר\"ע"
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "",
      "left": "0px",
      "text": "אפי' אין לך מה לאכול אא\"כ תמכור"
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "",
      "left": "0px",
      "text": "שער ראשך זקוק אתה ליתן לה כל"
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "",
      "left": "0px",
      "text": "הקרקע שיש לך: <b><span class=\"dh-divergent\">ש&quot;מ</span> אֵין</b>",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Nedarim 65b:7:1",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        5
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "",
      "left": "0px",
      "text": "<b>מְסַדְּרִין לְבַעַל חוֹב.</b> כלומר דהכל",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Nedarim 65b:7:1",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        5
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "",
      "left": "0px",
      "text": "גובין ממנו ונותנין לבעל חובו מדקאמר",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Nedarim 65b:7:1",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        5
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "",
      "left": "0px",
      "text": "ליה ר\"ע אתה מוכר שער ראשך",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Nedarim 65b:7:1",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        5
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "",
      "left": "0px",
      "text": "ותאכל והא קי\"ל במס' ערכין (<a href=\"/arakhin/23b\">דף כג:</a>)",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Nedarim 65b:7:1",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        5
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "",
      "left": "0px",
      "text": "ובב\"מ (<a href=\"/bava_metzia/114a\">דף קיד.</a>) דמניחין לו כלי",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Nedarim 65b:7:1",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        5
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "",
      "left": "0px",
      "text": "תשמישו ומטה ומפץ ושולחן ומזון ל'",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Nedarim 65b:7:1",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        5
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "",
      "left": "0px",
      "text": "יום: הכי קאמר ליה אפי' אתה",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Nedarim 65b:7:1",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        5
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "",
      "left": "0px",
      "text": "נותן לה כל אשר לך שאין לך לאכול",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Nedarim 65b:7:1",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        5
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "",
      "left": "0px",
      "text": "אלא שער ראשך אין קורעין לה",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Nedarim 65b:7:1",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        5
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "450px",
      "right": "",
      "left": "0px",
      "text": "כתובתה עד שתפרע לה הכל משלם. ואית דאמרי אין מסדרין",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Nedarim 65b:7:1",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        5
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "450px",
      "right": "",
      "left": "0px",
      "text": "לבעל חוב אין עושין לו סדר של חיות שאין מניחין לו מה",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Nedarim 65b:7:1",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        5
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "450px",
      "right": "",
      "left": "0px",
      "text": "שסדרו חכמים כדאמרינן התם שמניחין לו כלי תשמישו ומטה וכו':",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Nedarim 65b:7:1",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        5
      ]
    }
  ],
